<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    Block the "Emergency Approach" quest.

    That is the Royalty quest ShuttleCrash_Rescue (its name rule "[emergency] [landing]" renders as
    "Emergency Approach"): a damaged shuttle seeks to land, you defend its occupants against an
    attacking faction, then load the survivors onto a rescue shuttle. It's a normal random quest
    (rootSelectionWeight 1.9, not isRootSpecial), so the storyteller's GiveQuest roll picks it
    weighted by that value. Setting rootSelectionWeight to 0 drops it from the pool entirely.

    Global (no storyteller offers it), not scoped to The Antagonist - quest selection weight lives on
    the shared QuestScriptDef. Gated on Royalty via MayRequire so it's a no-op without the DLC.
-->
<Patch>
    <Operation Class="PatchOperationReplace" MayRequire="Ludeon.RimWorld.Royalty">
        <xpath>Defs/QuestScriptDef[defName="ShuttleCrash_Rescue"]/rootSelectionWeight</xpath>
        <value>
            <rootSelectionWeight>0</rootSelectionWeight>
        </value>
    </Operation>
</Patch>
